#   Last push  : 2025-11-28
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   nof1-tracker is "a command-line tool for tracking nof1.ai AI
#   Agent trading signals and automatically copying their futures
#   trades".  It polls nof1.ai's REST endpoint at a configurable
#   interval, reads the signal feed of a chosen AI agent (e.g.
#   GPT-5-Trader, GPT-Quant), runs an optional pre-trade risk
#   assessment, and either reports the signal or executes the
#   trade against a connected Binance Futures account (with
#   per-coin fixed-margin allocation, total-margin allocation,
#   isolated/crossed margin modes, price-tolerance guards, and
#   auto-exit at a configurable profit target).  Every trade
#   action and every periodic status update is mirrored to a
#   Telegram chat via the canonical node-telegram-bot-api SDK.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/index.ts — Commander
#                       v11 with `new Command()` chain)
#   nof1-tracker <SUBCOMMAND> [args...]
#
#   Subcommands:
#     agents                         List all available AI agents
#
#     follow <AGENT_NAME>            Follow an AI agent and copy
#                                    their trades
#       -r, --risk-only                Only do risk assessment;
#                                      skip trade execution
#       -i, --interval <SECS>          Polling interval
#                                      [default: 30]
#       -t, --price-tolerance <PCT>    Price tolerance threshold
#                                      [default: 1%]
#       -m, --total-margin <AMT>       Total margin
#                                      [default: 10 USDT]
#       --fixed-amount-per-coin <AMT>  Fixed margin per coin
#       --profit <PCT>                 Auto-exit at this profit
#                                      target (e.g. 30 for 30%)
#       --auto-refollow                Auto-refollow after profit
#                                      target exit
#       --margin-type <TYPE>           Margin mode (ISOLATED|
#                                                  CROSSED)
#                                      [default: CROSSED]
#
#     telegram-test                  Send a test Telegram message
#                                    (verifies BOT_TOKEN and chat
#                                    ID env wiring)
#
#     status                         Check system status and
#                                    configuration
#
#     profit                         Analyze profit/loss
#                                    statistics for futures trades
#       -s, --since <TIME>             Time filter
#                                      ("7d" | "2024-01-01" |
#                                       timestamp)
#       -p, --pair <SYMBOL>            Specific trading pair
#                                      (e.g. BTCUSDT)
#       --group-by <TYPE>              Group by symbol or all
#                                      [default: all]
#       --format <TYPE>                Output format (table|json)
#                                      [default: table]
#       --refresh                      Force refresh cache
#       --exclude-unrealized           Exclude unrealized P&L
#                                      from analysis
#       --unrealized-only              Show only unrealized P&L
#
#   Standard commander auto-flags:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Show version
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `node-telegram-bot-api ^0.66.0` declared
#   in package.json — `node-telegram-bot-api` is THE canonical
#   Node.js Telegram Bot library maintained by Yago González
#   (yagop/node-telegram-bot-api, 8.8K+ stars).  node-telegram-
#   bot-api exposes the `TelegramBot` constructor with `polling`,
#   `webHook`, `request` modes, the complete Bot API event
#   surface (`message`, `edited_message`, `callback_query`,
#   `inline_query`, `chosen_inline_result`, `channel_post`,
#   `edited_channel_post`, `shipping_query`, `pre_checkout_
#   query`, `poll`, `poll_answer`, `chat_member`, `my_chat_
#   member`, `chat_join_request`), typed model objects (Message,
#   User, Chat, MessageEntity, CallbackQuery, InlineQuery,
#   InlineKeyboardMarkup, ReplyKeyboardMarkup, ForceReply,
#   InputMedia*, Sticker, Document, PhotoSize, Audio, Video,
#   Voice, VideoNote, Animation, Location, Venue, Contact, Poll,
#   Dice, Game, Invoice, SuccessfulPayment), the typed
#   `sendMessage`, `sendPhoto`, `sendAudio`, `sendDocument`,
#   `sendVideo`, `sendAnimation`, `sendVoice`, `sendVideoNote`,
#   `sendMediaGroup`, `sendLocation`, `sendVenue`, `sendContact`,
#   `sendPoll`, `sendDice`, `sendChatAction`, `editMessageText`,
#   `editMessageCaption`, `editMessageMedia`, `editMessageReply
#   Markup`, `stopMessageLiveLocation`, `editMessageLiveLocation`,
#   `deleteMessage`, `forwardMessage`, `copyMessage`,
#   `sendPaidMedia`, `kickChatMember`, `banChatMember`,
#   `unbanChatMember`, `restrictChatMember`, `promoteChatMember`,
#   API methods, and the legacy + modern Bot API v6.x / v7.x /
#   v8.x feature set.  nof1-tracker's `src/services/telegram-
#   service.ts` constructs a `new TelegramBot(token, { polling:
#   false })` and dispatches signal-execution updates via
#   `bot.sendMessage(chatId, formatted, { parse_mode:
#   'MarkdownV2' })`.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/terryso/nof1-tracker/contents/package.json
#       → "node-telegram-bot-api": "^0.66.0"
#       → "commander": "^11.1.0"
#       → "bin": {"nof1-tracker": "dist/index.js"}
#     gh api repos/terryso/nof1-tracker/contents/src/index.ts
#       → const program = new Command();
#       → program.command('agents'|'follow <agent-name>'|
#                           'telegram-test'|'status'|'profit')
#       → import { handleTelegramCommand } from './commands'
#   This entry is the TS-Node=145 leader bump that CLOSES Axis
#   90 (Telegram Bot API / teloxide) at 1/1/1 three-language
#   symmetry — pairing Rust=teloxide via magnickolas/remindee-
#   bot (R949 _remindee-bot), Go=go-telegram-bot-api via RITlug/
#   teleirc (R950 _teleirc — R950 round-number commit landmark),
#   and TS-Node=node-telegram-bot-api via terryso/nof1-tracker
#   (this entry).  Triple-145 landmark on commit.  Axis 90 =
#   83rd axis closed.
#
#   No completion for `nof1-tracker` ships with Apple zsh
